 ABI-007-PST-001 is a Phase 1 / 2, multicenter, open-label, dose-finding study to assess the safety , tolerability, and preliminary efficacy of weekly nab-paclitaxel in pediatric patients with recurrent or refractory solid tumors (excluding brain tumors).

 The Phase 1 portion of the study, with a dose escalation design, ended and the recommended Phase 2 dose (RP2D) was determined as 240 mg/m2 IV in patients weighing > 10 kg and 11.

5 mg/kg in patients weighing 10 kg on Days 1, 8 and 15 of a 28-day cycle .

 The Phase 2 portion of the study will enroll additional patients at the RP2D into one of three solid tumor groups [Neuroblastomas, Rhabdomyosarcomas, Ewing's Sarcomas].

 Both phases of the study are open-label and conducted at multiple centers.

 The Phase 2 is using a Simon two-stage design to monitor patient enrollment for each group separately.

 The Rhabdomyosarcoma group did not reach the expected number of two responders out of fourteen efficacy eligible patients.

 Consequently, this group is stopped.

